<h3> 

Basic Commands
</h3></font>
Remember: To write something formatted you have to include it between the opening tag and the closing tag, if you forget to close the tag all the written text will be considered with the formatting of that tag
<p>
<br><br>
<bold>&#60;bold&gt;</bold> tag to start writing in bold
<br>
<bold>&#60;/bold&gt;</bold>tag to close the paragraph in bold
<br>
<br>
<br>
<bold>&#60;mainTitle&gt;</bold> 
tag to write the main title of the page

<br>
<bold>&#60;/mainTitle&gt;</bold> 
tag to close the main title of the page
<br>
<br>
<br>
<bold>&#60;subTitle&gt;</bold> 
tag to write a subtitle
<br>
<bold>&#60;/subTitle&gt;</bold>
tag to close the subtitle
 <br>
<br>
<br>
<bold>&#60;textLine&gt;</bold> 
tag to open a paragraph
<br>
<bold>&#60;/textLine&gt;</bold> 
tag to close a paragraph
<br>
<br>
<br>
<bold>&#60;color=</bold> 
tag to change the color of the text (the color must be inserted between '' and the tag must be closed after the color with the usual tag, ex: & # 60; color = 'red' & gt; now this text is red
<br>
<bold>&#60;/color&gt;</bold> 
tag to finish the color change (after this tag, the text will return to black)
<br>
<br>
<br>
<bold>&#60;table&gt;</bold> 
start of the table
<br>
<bold>&#60;/table&gt;</bold> 
end of the table
<br>
<br>
<br>
<bold>&#60;row&gt;</bold> 
start of a row in a table
<br>
<bold>&#60;/row&gt;</bold> 
end of a table row
<br>
<br>
<br>
<bold>&#60;column&gt;</bold> 
beginning of a column
<br>
<bold>&#60;/column&gt;</bold> 
end of a column
<br>
<br>
<br>
<bold>&#60;link=&gt;</bold> 
tag to insert a link
<br>
<bold>&#60;/link&gt;</bold> 
tag to close the link
<br>
ES: &#60;link = 'www.google.com'&gt;this is a link &#60;/link&gt; <br>This will cause "this is a link" to light blue and function as a link to www.google.com
<br>
<br>
<bold>&#60;EndLine&gt;</bold> 
tag to put every time you want to wrap
<br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
